# Fix Instagram-Like Video Feed: Autoplay, Preloading & Stability

The feed has multiple interrelated bugs causing videos to not autoplay, go black after 1 second (NativeSharedObjectNotFoundException), and show infinite spinners. Root causes span 6 files.

---

## Root Cause Analysis

| Bug | Root Cause | File(s) |
|-----|-----------|---------|
| Videos require a tap to play | `viewabilityConfig.itemVisiblePercentThreshold: 100` — in a mixed feed with partial posts, items rarely reach 100% visibility | `index.tsx` |
| Black screen + NativeSharedObjectNotFoundException | `video-manager.releaseOldest()` calls `player.release()` on a player still mounted in a `<VideoView>`, destroying the native object while JS still holds a ref | `video-manager.ts`, `post-media.tsx` |
| Infinite ActivityIndicator | Player created but never becomes `readyToPlay` because the status listener is attached *after* the status change fires (race condition) | `use-video-player.ts` |
| Only one video should play, but doesn't | `onViewableItemsChanged` only fires for the first viewable item, and stale closures in the hook miss visibility transitions | `index.tsx`, `use-video-player.ts` |
| Preloading not working | `nextPost` is passed to `Post` but never forwarded to `PostMedia`/`useManagedVideoPlayer` | `post.tsx` |
| Conditional hook violation | `usePostStore` called conditionally: `nextId ? usePostStore(...) : undefined` — breaks Rules of Hooks | `PostWrapper.tsx` |
| Double-tap/long-press interfere with playback | `handleTap` fires on *every* press (including the first tap of a double-tap), no debounce to distinguish single vs. double | `post-media.tsx` |

