## Proposed Changes

### Video Manager

#### [MODIFY] [video-manager.ts](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/src/lib/video-manager.ts)

Rewrite with these fixes:

- **Safe eviction**: `releaseOldest()` must skip players currently rendered in a `<VideoView>`. Add a `mountedPlayers` set that tracks which postIds have an active VideoView. Only evict unmounted players.
- **`replace()` instead of `release()`**: When evicting, call `player.replace(null)` to clear the source without destroying the native object, then `release()` only on truly unmounted players.
- **Single-play guarantee**: `play()` always pauses the previous player first (already done, but add guard for edge cases).
- **`hasPlayer()`**: Add a method to check if a player exists without creating one.
- **`mount()`/`unmount()`**: Track mounted VideoView lifecycle to inform eviction safety.
- **Raise max players to 5**: to accommodate preloading one extra without evicting a visible player.

---

### Video Player Hook

#### [MODIFY] [use-video-player.ts](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/hooks/use-video-player.ts)

- **Fix race condition**: After `getOrCreatePlayer()`, immediately check `player.status` and if already `readyToPlay`, set `isReady = true` and trigger play if visible — don't rely solely on the `statusChange` listener.
- **Fix stale closure**: Use `useRef` for all mutable state the event listeners depend on (`isVisible`, `postId`). Already using `isVisibleRef` but the `statusChange` callback still captures stale `postId`.
- **Cleanup on unmount**: Call `videoManager.unmount(postId)` in cleanup so the manager knows the player's VideoView is gone.
- **Mount tracking**: Call `videoManager.mount(postId)` when player is assigned.
- **Preload integration**: Keep the existing `nextPostUrl`/`nextPostId` useEffect (it works correctly).

---

### Feed Screen (FlatList)

#### [MODIFY] [index.tsx](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/app/(app)/(tabs)/index.tsx)

- **Lower viewability threshold**: Change `itemVisiblePercentThreshold` from `100` to `50` — this is Instagram's behavior; the most-visible post wins.
- **Pass `nextId`**: Compute and pass the next post ID to each `PostItem` for preloading.
- **Use `viewabilityConfigCallbackPairs`** instead of `onViewableItemsChanged` + `viewabilityConfig` to avoid the stale ref / recreation issue.
- **Add `removeClippedSubviews={true}`** for memory optimization.
- **Add `windowSize={5}`** to limit off-screen rendering.

---

### Post Wrapper

#### [MODIFY] [PostWrapper.tsx](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/src/components/home/posts/PostWrapper.tsx)

- **Fix conditional hook**: Always call `usePostStore` for `nextPost` (pass `null` selector when no `nextId`), never conditionally.

---

### Post Component

#### [MODIFY] [post.tsx](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/src/components/home/posts/post.tsx)

- **Forward next video info** to `PostMedia`: pass `nextPostId` and `nextPostUrl` props so `useManagedVideoPlayer` can preload.

---

### Post Media

#### [MODIFY] [post-media.tsx](file:///Users/flickios/Desktop/jaaspire/src/components/home/posts/post-media.tsx)

- **Guard against released players**: Always render `<VideoView>` when `player` exists (don't gate on `isReady`). `VideoView` can handle a player that's still loading — it just shows blank. Wrap in try-catch or guard with `player.status !== 'error'`.
- **Fix tap/double-tap conflict**: Use a `setTimeout` timer to distinguish single tap vs. double tap. Only fire single-tap action after the 300ms window if no second tap occurs.
- **Pass `nextPostUrl` and `nextPostId`** to `useManagedVideoPlayer`.

