## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

Since this is a React Native mobile app (Expo), verification must be done on device/simulator:

1. **Run the app**: `npx expo start` then open on iOS simulator or device
2. **Autoplay test**: Scroll the feed slowly — each video should auto-play as soon as ~50% is visible, without tapping
3. **Single playback**: Only one video should play at a time; scrolling to a new video should pause the previous
4. **Preloading**: Scroll to a video post — the *next* video in the feed should start instantly (no spinner) when it scrolls into view
5. **No black screens**: Scroll rapidly up and down 10+ times — no videos should go black or show the NativeSharedObjectNotFoundException error
6. **Double-tap like**: Double-tap an image/video — heart animation should appear, post should be liked
7. **Long-press pause**: Long-press a playing video — it should pause; releasing should resume
8. **Mute button**: Tap the mute/unmute button on a video — should toggle audio
9. **Screen unfocus**: Navigate to another tab and back — video should pause on leave and resume on return

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please confirm you can test on an iOS simulator or physical device, and let me know if any of the above changes need adjustment before I proceed.
